                                        <P class="p76 ft17">LOAN AGREEMENT</P>
                                        <P class="p77 ft3">This Loan Agreement is made and executed on this @Model.disbursementDate at @Model.centerName</P>
                                        <P class="p78 ft14">BY AND BETWEEN</P>
                                        <P class="p79 ft3">ASIRVAD Microfinance Limited, a company incorporated and registered under the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 having <NOBR>CIN-@Model.cinNo</NOBR> and having its registered office at @Model.holocation and corporate office at  @Model.holocation represented by its AuthorizedSignatory (Hereinafter referred to as the 'Lender / Company' which in expression shall mean and include its successors, legal heirs and permitted assignees)</P>
                                        <P class="p80 ft14">AND</P>
                                        <P class="p81 ft3">The Client Name (Hereinafter referred to as the Borrower/Co-Applicant) @Model.memberName W/D/o @Model.father being resident of the @Model.address address who in expression shall mean and include their successor,legal heir and permitted assignee)</P>
                                        <P class="p82 ft3">The Lender has approved and sanctioned the loan to Borrower based on the information provided by the Borrower in her loan application.</P>
                                        <P class="p83 ft33">WHEREAS further the Borrower have organized herself into a Group for the purpose of mutual guarantee, joint & several liability and the Borrower has guaranteed the repayment of loan of one another.</P>
                                        <P class="p82 ft3">The Borrower has signed Demand Promissory Note in favour of the Lender for the loan that they have availed.</P>
                                        <P class="p82 ft3">NOW, THEREFORE, the Lender and the Borrower as parties to this agreement hereby set forth their understanding and agree in writing as under:</P>
                                        <P class="p84 ft34">LOAN AMOUNT, INTEREST, REPAYMENT FREQUENCY & FEES</P>
                                        <P class="p85 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.1</SPAN><SPAN class="ft35">The Borrower hereby agreed to obtain the loan amount Rs- @Model.loanAmount from the Lender and thereby give a written acknowledgement of the same through this agreement along with the execution of various other documents.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p86 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.2</SPAN><SPAN class="ft35">The Borrower agree to repay the entire loan amount with the applicable interest as per diminishing balance method, within a term as stipulated in loan card.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p87 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.3</SPAN><SPAN class="ft35">The Borrower shall be charged Loan Processing Fee (Tax as applicable) and Insurance Premium (tax as applicable) before disbursement of loan. The Borrower understands that the pricing of the loan involves only three components viz; the interest charge, the processing charge and the insurance premium.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p88 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.4</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">The Borrower has chosen the repayment frequency and agree to pay as per the loan card as provided by the Company. Borrower understood that there will be a moratorium period for the first instalment, equivalent to the period of one instalment. Any furtherchanges in first repayment due date/amount, thereby, is as per mutual consent with Borrower by the Company.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p86 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.5</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">The Borrower under this agreement have agreed upon to repay the loan amount as mentioned in loan card without a prior noticeor demand from the Lender.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p89 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.6</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">In case any of the days of repayment as per loan card falls on a public holiday or the Lender's business holiday then the Borrower have agreed to repay the said installment amount on any other day as decided and intimated by the Lender either before or after the due date.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p90 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.7</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">The Borrower hereby agree to permit the Lender to change the Centre schedule such as day, time and place as per the convenience of both the parties and with the prior information to the Borrower. Further the Borrower confirm that they will adhere to the said change and make sure that they are available according to the new changed Centre meeting scheduled date, place and time.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p86 ft34">BORROWER OBLIGATION</P>
                                        <P class="p91 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.1</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower hereby confirm that they will be using the availed loan facility only for income generation activities/purpose as indicated in Loan Application. Any change in end use of funds shall be duly informed to the Company within 15 days of disbursement,failure of which may result in recall of loan. The Borrower hereby have agreed to the Company that, at any point of time whenever the Company intends to verify for the same.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p92 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.2</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">If the Borrower fail to utilize the loan amount as per the specified income generation activity/purpose, such act of the Borrower would tantamount to intentional misuse, criminal breach of trust and misappropriation and Lender is permitted to bring appropriate legal actions (civil or criminal or arbitration or other) against the Borrower.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p93 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.3</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower shall not give availed loan to anybody else.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p94 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.4</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower hereby confirms that they have not availed loan facility from more than 2 MFIs including this Company as on the date of this disbursement, and that she will not become member of more than one Joint Liability Group/Self Help Group.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p95 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.5</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower here by confirms that their household income is not more than Rs.2,00,000/- and her indebtedness is not more than Rs. </SPAN><NOBR>1,25,000/-.</NOBR></P>
                                        <P class="p96 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.6</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower under this agreement undertake jointly and severally to keep this agreement as confidential and also undertake not to provide any information or copies of the same unless the Borrower under this agreement are legally required to do so by any law/ statute and in such circumstances, they shall obtain prior written consent of the Company to provide the same.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p97 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.7</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower hereby confirm that they have not paid or provided any security deposit, any collateral or any form of monetarydeposit directly or indirectly to the Company or its stafffor availing this loan.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p98 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.8</SPAN><SPAN class="ft37">The Borrower understands that the loan application form and the copies of KYC documents obtained for the purpose of processing loan shall not be returned.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p99 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.9</SPAN><SPAN class="ft38">The Borrower understands and agrees that all repayments shall be made only in mutually agreed upon centre meeting location orat Company's Branch premises. However, the loan disbursement will be directly credited into her bank account post deduction of applicable processing fee and insurance premium plus taxes.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p98 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.10</SPAN><SPAN class="ft39">The Borrower agreed to pay </SPAN><NOBR>non-refundable</NOBR> Group Term Life Insurance premium as per the norms.</P>
                                        <P class="p100 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.11</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower shall notify the Company of any changes in her contact details viz. Address, mobile number, KYC information within next centre meeting. The Company will not be held responsible for any delay in transmission of such information and will be free to take any action, under this agreement, towards collection of the outstanding loan amount.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p101 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.12</SPAN><SPAN class="ft41">Whenever the Borrower wishes to change the centre/branch, the Borrower shall make explicit request in writing to the Company which will be taken in to consideration within 21 days.</SPAN></P>
                                        <P class="p102 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.13</SPAN><SPAN class="ft41">The Borrower hereby consents to the company to share her KYC data and Credit history to Credit bureau agencies, Rating agencies,regulators, Banks /Funding agencies, Government offices based on the guidelines from RBI from time to time.</SPAN></P>
                                    </DIV>
                                </DIV>
                                <DIV id="page_4">

                                    <P class="p103 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.14</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower need not to pay any commission or charges other than mentioned in loan card to any individual including staff of the Company.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p104 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.15</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower hereby agree to comply with all company guidelines and processes while availing and repayment of the loan. TheBorrower also understand that these guidelines/ processes are subject to change from time to time as per Regulatory guidelines(issued by Government, RBI, SRO... etc.)</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p105 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.16</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower hereby severally and jointly undertake that they will never indulge in any activity which results in delays in repaymentsor stopping repayments by means of provoking, diverting or influencing the other Borrower of the group/centre or any otherborrower of the Company in either the same centre or same village or other villages under any circumstances.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p106 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.17</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower hereby allows the Company to initiate the insurance claim process on behalf of Borrower in event of death as per the Insurance Policy. For the said purposes, the Borrower agrees with the company to retains the insurance policy under their custody for speedy processing of the claim.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p107 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">2.18</SPAN><SPAN class="ft40">The Borrower hereby confirm that in case due date falls on holidays or a public holiday or the Company business holiday then the client can repay the said instalment amount on any other day as confirmed by Company staff either before or after the due date.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p108 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">2.19</SPAN><SPAN class="ft41">The Borrower hereby confirm that this agreement and policies & procedures of the Company has been read to her by Company's staff and someone independently in a language that she understands, and she has clearly understood all the terms and conditions under this agreement and policies & procedures of the Company irrespective of her literacy levels.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p109 ft34">LENDERS RIGHTS & OBLIGATION</P>
                                    <P class="p110 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.1</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Lender shall provide Loan Card containing repayment schedule to the Borrower as agreed and signed by the parties to this agreement. The terms and specifications incorporated in loan card with reference to this agreement have been unconditionally agreed by the parties.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p111 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.2</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Lender will not charge any penalty for delayed repayments. However, any delay in repayment by clients can adversely affect their credibility and their chances of getting further loans. This decision will be at the sole discretion of the Lender. Furthermore,any wilful delay in repayments beyond 30 days will give the Lender the right to take due legal action as deemed necessary to recollect any outstanding amount of the loan along with other charges as applicable.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p112 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.3</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Borrower under this agreement agree to allow the Lender to securitize or assign the loan instalments/ receivable due or outstanding due from the Borrower in favour of any Bank, NBFC, Holding company, Financial Institution, MFI or any other entitywhatsoever and also authorize the Lender to become a collection agent for such entity or appoint any one as a collection agentduring the term of their loan for any reason whatsoever.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p113 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.4</SPAN><SPAN class="ft38">The Lender commits & undertakes to protect the privacy of the Borrower Information & data.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p114 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.5</SPAN><SPAN class="ft38">The Lender will not charge any penalty on prepayment of loan.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p113 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.6</SPAN><SPAN class="ft38">Settlement of loan will be confirmed by mentioning in the passbook in front of the client.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p115 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.7</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Lender hereby undertakes to be committed to deal fairly with the Borrower and abide by its own Fair Practices Code, RBI's Fair Practices Code & Other Industry Fair Practices Code &Code of Conduct in view of the fair and transparent lending policy as per the guidelines of the regulating authority.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p116 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.8</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Lender confirms that grant of loan is not linked to any other product /services offered by the MFI or third party.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p117 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.9</SPAN><SPAN class="ft42">The Lender reserves the right to recalling the loan/ accelerating payment of the outstanding loan amount anytime from the clientsin case the client breaches any of the terms & conditions as mentioned herein this loan agreement.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p118 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.10</SPAN><SPAN class="ft43">The Company staff will not collect any other amount from client except for due Loan instalments, Insurance Fees and ProcessingFees, in cash or any other form. The Company will acknowledge every financial transaction by entry in their passbook/any form of communication such as receipts, SMS, mails etc.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p119 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.11</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">The Company undertakes and confirms to train its staff on Fair Practices, ethical behaviour with an intention to prevent inappropriate collection and will be accountable for preventing inappropriate staff behaviour and timely grievance redressal.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p120 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.12</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">The Borrower under this agreement specifically permit the Lender and its authorized representatives or staff to visit the homeor dwelling place or working place of the Borrower or the authorized representatives of the Borrower for collection of loan dues within the compliance of the Lender's or RBI's Fair Practices Code / Notifications.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p121 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">3.13</SPAN><SPAN class="ft36">Before providing any </SPAN><NOBR>non-financial</NOBR> products to the Borrower, Lender will take confirmation from her.</P>
                                    <P class="p114 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">3.14</SPAN><SPAN class="ft35">In case of any complaint/grievance, client can call company TOLL Free number </SPAN><NOBR>1800-270-1146&</NOBR> <NOBR>1800 102 1080</NOBR> OR Local Branch Manager.</P>
                                    <P class="p122 ft34">JURISDICTION & GENERAL TERMS</P>
                                    <P class="p123 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">1.1</SPAN><SPAN class="ft44"> All disputes arising in connection with this agreement, at any time, shall be settled among the parties by discussions but if they fail to arrive at a consensus settlement, the same may be   referred to the Sole Arbitrator, to be appointed by the Company, whose decision shall be final and binding on both the parties. The expenses for the same shall be borne by the Borrower.  In the event of incapacity or resignation or death of the Sole Arbitrator so appointed, Company shall be entitled to appoint another Arbitrator in place of the earlier Arbitrator, and the proceedings shall continue from the stage at which the predecessor had left it. The venue of the arbitration shall be at Chennai or such other place as may be decided by the Company and the arbitration proceedings shall be governed by the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996 with any statutory modifications and re-enactments or amendments thereof and shall be in English language. The Arbitrator's Award shall be in writing. The Arbitrator shall also decide on the costs of the arbitration proceedings.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p124 ft3"><SPAN class="ft31">1.2</SPAN><SPAN class="ft45">This Agreement shall be executed in two counterparts one to be retained by each party, both of which taken together shall constitute one and the same agreement.</SPAN></P>
                                    
                                    <P class="p116 ft3"><SPAN class="ft3">1.3</SPAN><SPAN class="ft44">No provision or terms of the agreement hereby accepted by both parties herein shall be waived off without the prior consent of Lender.</SPAN></P>
                                    <P class="p125 ft3">I, the undersigned, have willingly executed this Loan and Joint Liability Guarantee Agreement on the @Model.applnDate and under this agreement hereby agree to the <NOBR>above-mentioned</NOBR> terms and conditions of the Loan and Joint Liability Guarantee Agreement.</P>
                                    <P class="p116 ft3">I, the undersigned, have received the physical copy of Loan and Joint Liability Guarantee Agreement on the <NOBR>above-mentioned</NOBR> date of execution of the agreement.</P>
                                    <P class="p126 ft3">IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties herein under have set their hands the day and year hereinabove mentioned.</P>
